# Chapter 14 — Autogen

> NOT YET SHIPPED · The `sakura/*` autogen verbs described in this chapter are aspirational and not yet in the language runtime. They are on the v1.5+ roadmap. This chapter documents the intended interface.

The `sakura/` verb family bridges the language and the model. When you can't remember a form, ask. When your code is verbose, rewrite. When you don't understand a snippet, explain.

## `sakura/complete`

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(sakura/complete \"(map (lambda (n) (* n \")
</pre>

## `sakura/rewrite`

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(sakura/rewrite '(if x (if y (if z a b) b) b)
                :as 'and-chain)
</pre>

## `sakura/explain`

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(sakura/explain '(let loop ((i 0)) (if (> i 3) 'done (loop (+ i 1)))))
</pre>

> **Sakura says**
>
> `sakura/*` verbs go through me — literally. When you hit one, your REPL sends the form up to the model, I respond, and the answer becomes the return value. If the model is offline, the verb errors with `sakura/unavailable` — the code you wrote is fine, the wire just isn't up.

> **Warning**
>
> These verbs cost tokens. In the browser book, they're rate-limited to prevent runaway loops. In the local CLI, no limit — you pay per call.

